SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 41
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Warren Morris upon receiving the 2026 Louisiana Sports
Ambassador Award and on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports Hall
of Fame.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Warren Morris upon receiving the 2026 Louisiana Sports Ambassador Award
3 and on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Sports Writers Association established the Ambassador
5 Award to recognize individuals who have made long-term exemplary contributions to the
6 perception of Louisiana through their ties to the state's sports landscape; and
7 WHEREAS, the Ambassador Award is not bestowed annually, but rather on
8 occasion, as determined by the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Selection Committee and, this
9 year, the Selection Committee has selected Warren Morris as the third recipient of this
10 esteemed award; and
11 WHEREAS, Warren Morris, a native and resident of Alexandria, earned national
12 recognition as a member of the Louisiana State University (LSU) Tigers baseball program
13 and became forever associated with one of the most dramatic finishes in the history of the
14 College World Series; and
15 WHEREAS, on June 8, 1996, Morris delivered a legendary two-out, two-run
16 walk-off home run to secure the national championship for LSU, providing LSU with a
17 dramatic victory in the 1996 College World Series and cementing his place in the annals of
18 college baseball history; and
