1 WHEREAS, Morris went on to play parts of five seasons in major league baseball
2 before retiring from professional baseball and returning to his hometown of Alexandria,
3 where he has remained active in the community while working in the banking industry and
4 supporting numerous civic and charitable causes; and
5 WHEREAS, while in high school, Morris earned letters in baseball, basketball, and
6 cross-country and, in recognition of his achievements and lasting legacy, he was selected in
7 2024 as an inaugural inductee into the Bolton High School Hall of Fame.
8 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
9 commend Warren Morris upon receiving the 2026 Louisiana Sports Ambassador Award and
10 on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
12 Warren Morris.
